gn:left;\"|\n|-\n|3\n|{{yes2}}Win\n|3\u20130\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{flagicon|NGA}} Rasheed Lawal\n|{{abbr|KO|Knockout}}\n|1 (4), {{small|1:52}}\n|19 Sep 2015\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{flagicon|USA}} {{small|Resorts World, [[Queens, New York]], U.S.}}\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|\n|-\n|2\n|{{yes2}}Win\n|2\u20130\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{flagicon|DOM}} Juan Carlos Santos\n|{{abbr|TKO|Technical knockout}}\n|2 (4), {{small|2:02}}\n|15 Aug 2015\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{flagicon|DOM}} {{small|Multiuso Leo Tavarez, [[Salvale\u00f3n de Hig\u00fcey|Hig\u00fcey]], Dominican Republic}}\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|\n|-\n|1\n|{{yes2}}Win\n|1\u20130\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{flagicon|USA}} Jeff Souffrant\n|{{abbr|UD|Unanimous decision}}\n|4\n|24 Jul 2015\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{flagicon|USA}} {{small|Masonic Temple, [[Brooklyn, New York]], U.S.}}\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Adames, Carlos}}\n[[Category:Welterweight boxers]]\n[[Category:1994 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Dominican Republic male boxers]]\n[[Category:People from Comendador]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Dominican boxer (1993- )}}\n{{Infobox boxer\n| name           = Carlos Adames\n| image          = \n| image_size     = \n| alt            = \n| caption        = \n| realname       = \n| nickname       = \n| weight         = [[Welterweight]]\n| height         = 1.81 m\n| reach          = 185cm\n| nationality    = [[Dominican Republic|Dominican]]\n| birth_name     = \n| birth_date     = {{Birth date and age|1994|05|07}}\n| birth_place    = [[Comendador, Dominican Republic|Comendador]], [[Dominican Republic]]\n| death_date     = <!-- {{death date and age|year of death|month of death|day of death|year of birth|month of birth|day of birth}} -->\n| death_place    = \n| style          = [[Orthodox stance|Orthodox]]\n| total          = 19\n| wins           = 18\n| KO             = 14\n| losses         = 1\n| draws          = \n| no contests    = \n| embed          = <!-- \"yes\" allows infobox embedding -->\n}}\n\n'''Carlos Adames''' (born 7 May 1994) is a Dominican [[professional boxer]]. As of September 2019, Adames is ranked as the world\u2019s tenth best active [[light middleweight]] by [[BoxRec]] and the [[Transnational Boxing Rankings Board]].\n\nAdames represented the Dominican Republic on the [[World Series of Boxing]] between 2014 and 2015, accumulating a 4-2 record.<ref name=\"worldseriesboxing\">{{cite web|url=https://www.worldseriesboxing.com/boxers/adames-carlos/|title=ADAMES Carlos|website=World Series Boxing|accessdate=2017-11-03}}</ref>\n\nAdames made his professional debut on July 2015, defeating Jeff Souffrant by [[unanimous decision]] after four rounds. Adames won the vacant [[World Boxing Association|WBA]] Fedecaribe [[welterweight]] title in his seventh bout, beating Kelly Figueroa. He won another vacant title in his next fight, defeating Patrick Lopez with a fourth round [[technical knockout]] for the WBA Fedelatin title.<ref name=\"wbaboxing\">{{cite web|url=http://www.wbaboxing.com/regions-fedelatin/carlos-adames-defends-wba-fedelatin-welterweight-title|title=Carlos Adames Defends WBA Fedelatin Welterweight Title &#8211; World Boxing Association|website=wbaboxing.com|accessdate=2017-11-03}}</ref>\n\nOn July 2017, Adames defeated welterweight contender [[Carlos Molina (Mexican boxer)|Carlos Molina]] by [[unanimous decision]] (110-98, 110-98, 109-99) after eleven rounds. Adames put on a dominant performance, dropping Molina in round and outclassing him through the rest of the fight. However, the fight ended a 10-fight knockout streak for Adames.<ref name=\"boxingscene\">{{cite web|url=http://www.boxingscene.com/carlos-adames-drops-decisions-carlos-molina-results--118901|title=Carlos Adames Drops, Decisions Carlos Molina in WBA Clash - Boxing News|website=boxingscene.com|accessdate=2017-11-03}}</ref>\n\nOn November, Adames was scheduled to face Frank Rojas in a welterweight bout as part of the 96th WBA Convention in [[Medell\u00edn]], but the bout was called off after he failed to make weight.\n\n==Professional boxing record==\n{{BoxingRecordSummary\n|ko-wins=14\n|ko-losses=\n|dec-wins=4\n|dec-losses=\n|dq-wins=\n|dq-losses=\n}}\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center; font-size:95%\"\n|-\n!{{abbr|No.|Number}}\n!Result\n!Record\n!Opponent\n!Type\n!Round, time\n!Date\n!Location\n!Notes\n|-\n|18\n|{{yes2}}Win\n|18\u20130\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{flagicon|USA}} [[Patrick Day]]\n|UD\n|10\n|28 Jun, 2019\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{flagicon|USA}} {{small|[[Pechanga Resort & Casino]], [[Temecula, California]], U.S.}}\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{small|Retained NABF and WBO NABO super welterweight titles}}\n|-\n|17\n|{{yes2}}Win\n|17\u20130\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{flagicon|USA}} Frank Galarza\n|TKO\n|4 (10), {{small|1:07}}\n|20 Apr, 2019\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{flagicon|USA}} {{small|Madison Square Garden, New York, U.S.}}\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{small|Retained NABF Super welterweight title<br>Won WBO NABO super welterweight title}}\n|-\n|16\n|{{yes2}}Win\n|16\u20130\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{flagicon|VEN}} Juan Ruiz\n|KO\n|3 (8), {{small|1:57}}\n|18 Jan, 2019\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{flagicon|USA}} {{small|Turning Stone Resort & Casino, Verona, U.S.}}\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{small|}}\n|-\n|15\n|{{yes2}}Win\n|15\u20130\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{flagicon|USA}} Joshua Conley\n|TKO\n|2 (10), {{small|2:17}}\n|13 Oct, 2018\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{flagicon|USA}} {{small|[[CHI Health Center Omaha|CHI Health Center]], Omaha, Nebraska, U.S.}}\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{small|Won vacant NABF Super welterweight title}}\n|-\n|14\n|{{yes2}}Win\n|14\u20130\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{flagicon|MEX}} [[Alejandro Barrera]]\n|UD\n|10\n|12 May 2018\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{flagicon|USA}} {{small|Madison Square Garden, New York, New York, USA}}\n|style=